    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Peace Commission</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegraphic instructions as to Philippine Islands received. We will, unless
                    otherwise instructed, present on Monday an article to provide for cession of the
                    whole group, together with statement that we are prepared to insert in the
                    treaty a stipulation for the assumption by the United States of any existing
                    indebtedness of Spain incurred for necessary works and improvements of a pacific
                    character in Philippine Islands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
